getPath

public java.awt.Shape getPath(OneDimensionalDataSet reference,
                              java.awt.geom.Rectangle2D viewDataSpace,
                              java.awt.geom.Rectangle2D viewCanvasSpace)
Maps the dataset relative to another set. The mapping is done from the data space (i.e. the units of the data sets) to the graph space (i.e. the units of the canvas being drawn on). The mapping requires:
  1. A data set to draw relative to. The relative set is used for the x-axis and this set is on the y-axis.
  2. The data space of the viewport.
  3. The canvas space of the viewport.
      4. Specified by:
      getPath in interface OneDimensionalDataSet
